## ğŸš¦ THE TDD CYCLE (Your Daily Routine)

### For EACH Feature/Task:

#### 1ï¸âƒ£ RED - Write Failing Test
```javascript
// tests/unit/snake.test.js
describe('Snake', () => {
  test('should initialize with 3 segments', () => {
    const snake = new Snake();
    expect(snake.segments.length).toBe(3);
  });
});

// Run: npm test
// Result: FAIL âŒ
```

#### 2ï¸âƒ£ GREEN - Write Minimum Code
```javascript
// src/entities/Snake.js
class Snake {
  constructor() {
    this.segments = [
      { x: 10, y: 10 },
      { x: 9, y: 10 },
      { x: 8, y: 10 }
    ];
  }
}

// Run: npm test
// Result: PASS âœ…
```

#### 3ï¸âƒ£ REFACTOR - Improve Code
```javascript
// Optimize, add comments, improve structure
class Snake {
  constructor(gridSize = 20) {
    const centerX = Math.floor(gridSize / 2);
    this.segments = [
      { x: centerX, y: centerX },
      { x: centerX - 1, y: centerX },
      { x: centerX - 2, y: centerX }
    ];
  }
}

// Run: npm test
// Result: PASS âœ… (still)
```

#### 4ï¸âƒ£ COMMIT - Save Your Work
```bash
git add .
git commit -m "feat: implement Snake entity with movement"
git push origin feature/snake-entity
```

**Repeat this cycle for each test!**

