## ğŸ® QUICK COMMAND REFERENCE

```bash
# Development
npm run dev              # Start dev server
npm test                 # Run tests
npm test -- --watch     # Watch mode
npm run build            # Production build
npm run lint             # Check code quality
npm run lint:fix         # Auto-fix issues

# Git
git status               # Current status
git log --oneline -5     # Last 5 commits
git branch -a            # All branches
git pull origin main     # Get latest
git push origin feature  # Push branch

# Debugging
npm test -- --verbose   # Detailed test output
npm run analyze          # Bundle analysis
npm run dev -- --port 3000  # Different port
```

---

## ğŸš¨ IF YOU GET STUCK

### Problem: `npm install` fails
```bash
# Clear cache and retry
npm cache clean --force
rm -rf node_modules package-lock.json
npm install
```

### Problem: Tests not updating
```bash
# Clear Jest cache
npx jest --clearCache
npm test
```

### Problem: Webpack dev server won't start
```bash
# Kill process on port 8080 and restart
# macOS/Linux:
lsof -ti:8080 | xargs kill -9
# Windows: Use Task Manager
npm run dev
```

### Problem: Git conflicts
```bash
# Abort merge if unsure
git merge --abort

# Or resolve conflicts manually
# Then: git add . && git commit -m "fix: merge conflicts"
```

### Problem: Want to undo last commit
```bash
# If not pushed:
git reset --soft HEAD~1    # Keep changes
git reset --hard HEAD~1    # Discard changes
```

